name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(ggplot2)

# 1. LOAD AND PREP DATA ---------------------------------------------------

# Define the filename
fn <- "data.csv"

if (!file.exists(fn)) {
  download.file("https://github.com/JiriStipl/GRP_ANCOVA_webR/blob/main/data.csv", destfile = "data.csv")
}

# Read CSV
d <- read.csv(fn, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)


# 1. Convert GROUP
# Check the actual values in the column
u_group <- unique(na.omit(d$group))

if (all(u_group %in% c(0, 1))) {
  # Logic for 0=HC, 1=MDD (Common in Python/Machine Learning data)
  d$group <- factor(d$group, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("Healthy Control", "MDD"))
} else {
  # Logic for 1=HC, 2=MDD (Common in SPSS data)
  d$group <- factor(d$group, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("Healthy Control", "MDD"))
}

# 2. Convert GENDER
u_gender <- unique(na.omit(d$gender))

if (all(u_gender %in% c(0, 1))) {
  # Logic for 0/1. ASSUMPTION: 0=Male, 1=Female (Standard dummy coding)
  # If your data is reversed, swap the labels below.
  d$gender <- factor(d$gender, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("Male", "Female"))
} else {
  # Logic for 1/2.
  d$gender <- factor(d$gender, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c("Male", "Female"))
}

# Variable Name Mapping (For pretty UI labels)
dv_choices <- c(
  "Memory Error (Set Size 1)" = "setsize1_CSD",
  "Memory Error (Set Size 2)" = "setsize2_CSD",
  "Memory Error (Set Size 4)" = "setsize4_CSD",
  "Memory Error (Set Size 6)" = "setsize6_CSD",
  "Resource Variability (TAU)" = "TAU",
  "Initial Resources (J1)" = "J1",
  "Cognitive Ability (IQ)" = "IQ" # Added as potential outcome
)

cov_choices <- c(
  "Color Perception (base_CSD)" = "base_CSD",
  "Age" = "age",
  "Cognitive Ability (IQ)" = "IQ",
  "Depression Severity (BDI)" = "BDI"
)

# 2. UI LAYOUT ------------------------------------------------------------
ui <- fluidPage(
  
  titlePanel("ANCOVA: vWM & Depression (Kong et al., 2025)"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      h4("1. Dependent Variable"),
      selectInput("dv", "Dependent Variable (Outcome):", choices = dv_choices),
      
      hr(),
      h4("2. Grouping Variables"),
      checkboxGroupInput("ivs", "Independent Variables:",
                         choices = c("Group (MDD vs HC)" = "group",
                                     "Sex (Male vs Female)" = "gender"),
                         selected = c("group", "gender")),
      
      hr(),
      h4("3. Statistical Adjustments"),
      p(class = "text-muted", "Select variables to 'control for' in the ANCOVA model."),
      checkboxGroupInput("covs", "Covariates:",
                         choices = cov_choices,
                         selected = "base_CSD"), # Default to the "Good" covariate
      
      hr(),
      helpText("Note: The plots update automatically.")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      tabsetPanel(
        # TAB 1: The "Figure 3" Replica
        tabPanel("Group Comparison", 
                 br(),
                 h4("Group Differences (Mean +/- SE)"),
                 p("The bars show the raw data. The significance lines (stars) come from your specific Model."),
                 plotOutput("barPlot", height = "500px")
        ),
        
        # TAB 2: Effect Sizes
        tabPanel("Effect Sizes (Coefficients)", 
                 br(),
                 h4("Regression Coefficients"),
                 p("How much does the effect size changes when you add covariates?"),
                 plotOutput("coefPlot", height = "450px")
        ),
        
        # TAB 3: Raw Output
        tabPanel("Model Summary", 
                 br(),
                 verbatimTextOutput("modelSum")
        )
      )
    )
  )
)

# 3. SERVER LOGIC ---------------------------------------------------------
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  # --- DYNAMIC UI LOGIC ---
  # Prevent selecting IQ as both DV and Covariate
  observeEvent(input$dv, {
    current_covs <- input$covs
    
    if (input$dv == "IQ") {
      # Remove IQ from covariate choices
      updateCheckboxGroupInput(session, "covs",
                               choices = cov_choices[cov_choices != "IQ"],
                               selected = current_covs[current_covs != "IQ"])
    } else {
      # Restore IQ to covariate choices (maintain selection state)
      updateCheckboxGroupInput(session, "covs",
                               choices = cov_choices,
                               selected = current_covs)
    }
  })
  
  # --- MODEL BUILDING ---
  current_model <- reactive({
    req(input$ivs) # Require at least one IV
    
    # Combine IVs and Covariates
    predictors <- c(input$ivs, input$covs)
    
    # Formula construction
    f <- as.formula(paste(input$dv, "~", paste(predictors, collapse = " + ")))
    
    lm(f, data = d)
  })
  
  # --- PLOT 1: BAR CHART WITH STARS (The "Fig 3" Replica) ---
  # --- PLOT 1: BAR CHART WITH STARS (The "Fig 3" Replica) ---
  output$barPlot <- renderPlot({
    req(input$ivs) # Require at least one IV
    
    # 1. Dynamic Aggregation based on selected IVs
    # We construct a formula like "TAU ~ group + gender" dynamically
    agg_formula <- as.formula(paste(input$dv, "~", paste(input$ivs, collapse = "+")))
    
    # Calculate Mean and SE
    # (Using base R aggregate to ensure WebR compatibility without dplyr)
    agg_res <- aggregate(agg_formula, data = d, 
                         FUN = function(x) c(mean = mean(x, na.rm=TRUE), 
                                             se = sd(x, na.rm=TRUE)/sqrt(length(x))))
    
    # Clean up the weird matrix output from aggregate
    plot_data <- cbind(agg_res[, input$ivs, drop=FALSE], agg_res[[input$dv]])
    
    # 2. Extract P-value for the significance bracket
    # We prioritize showing the "Group" effect because that's the focus of the MDD lesson
    mod <- current_model()
    coefs <- summary(mod)$coefficients
    
    # Find the row for Group (MDD). 
    group_row <- grep("group", rownames(coefs))
    
    if (length(group_row) > 0 && "group" %in% input$ivs) {
      pval <- coefs[group_row, 4]
      
      # Determine Star Label
      if (pval < 0.001) { star_label <- "***" }
      else if (pval < 0.01) { star_label <- "**" }
      else if (pval < 0.05) { star_label <- "*" }
      else { star_label <- "ns" }
      
      show_bracket <- TRUE
    } else {
      star_label <- ""
      show_bracket <- FALSE
    }
    
    # 3. Calculate Y-positions for the bracket
    y_max <- max(plot_data$mean + plot_data$se)
    bracket_y <- y_max * 1.10
    label_y <- y_max * 1.15
    
    # 4. Draw Plot based on selection
    p <- ggplot(plot_data) + theme_classic(base_size = 18)
    
    # LOGIC: How to map X and Fill based on checkboxes
    if ("group" %in% input$ivs && "gender" %in% input$ivs) {
      # Case A: Both Group and Gender (Like Fig 3)
      p <- p + aes(x = group, y = mean, fill = gender) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge(0.9), width = 0.7) +
        geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - se, ymax = mean + se), 
                      position = position_dodge(0.9), width = 0.2) +
        scale_fill_manual(values = c("Male" = "#999999", "Female" = "#56B4E9"))
      
    } else if ("group" %in% input$ivs) {
      # Case B: Only Group
      p <- p + aes(x = group, y = mean, fill = group) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 0.6) +
        geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - se, ymax = mean + se), width = 0.2) +
        scale_fill_manual(values = c("Healthy Control" = "#999999", "MDD" = "#56B4E9")) +
        theme(legend.position = "none")
      
    } else if ("gender" %in% input$ivs) {
      # Case C: Only Gender
      p <- p + aes(x = gender, y = mean, fill = gender) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 0.6) +
        geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean - se, ymax = mean + se), width = 0.2) +
        scale_fill_manual(values = c("Male" = "#999999", "Female" = "#56B4E9")) +
        theme(legend.position = "none")
    }
    
    # Add the bracket if Group is involved (The main lesson)
    if (show_bracket) {
      # We place the bracket over the main group categories
      p <- p + 
        annotate("segment", x = 1, xend = 1, y = y_max, yend = bracket_y) + 
        annotate("segment", x = 2, xend = 2, y = y_max, yend = bracket_y) + 
        annotate("segment", x = 1, xend = 2, y = bracket_y, yend = bracket_y) + 
        annotate("text", x = 1.5, y = label_y, label = star_label, size = 8, fontface = "bold")
    }
    
    # Final labels
    p <- p + labs(y = input$dv, title = paste("Comparison of", input$dv),
                  subtitle = paste("Significance test controls for:", paste(input$covs, collapse=", ")))
    
    p
  })
  
  # --- PLOT 2: COEFFICIENT PLOT (Effect Sizes) ---
  output$coefPlot <- renderPlot({
    mod <- current_model()
    coefs <- summary(mod)$coefficients
    ci <- confint(mod)
    
    plot_data <- data.frame(
      Term = rownames(coefs),
      Estimate = coefs[,1],
      Lower = ci[,1],
      Upper = ci[,2],
      Pval = coefs[,4]
    )
    
    # Clean up labels
    plot_data$Significance <- ifelse(plot_data$Pval < 0.05, "Significant", "Not Sig")
    plot_data <- plot_data[plot_data$Term != "(Intercept)", ]
    
    ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = reorder(Term, abs(Estimate)), y = Estimate, color = Significance)) +
      geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
      geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Lower, ymax = Upper), width = 0.2, size = 1) +
      geom_point(size = 4) +
      coord_flip() +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("Significant" = "firebrick", "Not Sig" = "grey60")) +
      labs(x = "Predictor", y = "Beta Coefficient", 
           title = "How big is the effect?"
           #subtitle = "Watch the 'groupMDD' bar shrink when you add IQ!"
           ) +
      theme_bw(base_size = 16)
  })
  
  # --- TEXT SUMMARY ---
  output$modelSum <- renderPrint({
    summary(current_model())
  })
}

# 4. RUN APP --------------------------------------------------------------
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)


# GRP_ANCOVA
